        <abstract>
            <p>Sends plants from France.</p> 
<p>J. B. E. Bornet of Antibes, working in G. A. Thuret’s garden, finds <hi rend="italic">Cistus</hi> hybrids do not follow the old dictum of having the mother’s foliage and the father’s habit. Bornet is engaged in long-term study.</p> 
            <p>JTM seeks invitation to Down.</p>
        </abstract>
